<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-76-1006 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper describes the software architecture of the Direct Access HandlingSubsystem (DAHSS), which is an Automated Storage/Retrieval System (AS/RS)type robot. It was developed by IBM San Jose for use within Class 100cleanroom environments at several of its world wide facilities. The focusof this paper is the open system architectural approach that simplifiesintegration with other shop floor equipment and systems. In particular,the message stacking capability and the Virtual CPU concepts are discussed.</TEXT></DOC>